  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-75a0a546-7fff-7362-36bc-9b41d13e8c87\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:6pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">This staff has 7 charges, and can be used in three different ways.. While holding the staff, you can use an action for one of the following effects. You may supply the verbal component of each effect, or allow the staff to generate it on its own.Â  Each has a save DC of 15.</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:6pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:bold;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.cdrYKaFi98YWaBMw]{Vicious Mockery}</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> (1 charge): If no insult is uttered by the wielder, the staff itself calls out. The DM should make up an appropriate insult on the spot, or roll on the sample insults table here. The spell scales according to the level of the wielder (so a 1st level character activating the staff would deal 1d4 damage, a 5th level character would deal 2d4, and so on).</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:6pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:bold;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Lingering Insult</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> (3 charges). The staff can be used to cast @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.7v06rdmUakoTk1LQ]{Magic Mouth}, except that any creature triggering the effect will also be subject to Vicious Mockery regardless of the actual message. While the Magic Mouth effect is active, the staff cannot regain the charges spent to create it.</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The staff regains 1d6+1 charges at dawn. If you expend the staff's last charge, roll a d20. On a 1, the staff crumbles to ash and is unusable.</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:italic;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">\"It's not that dangerous, really. Sometimes I point it at myself just to see what it says. Hilarious!\"</span></p>",
